This paper focuses on set-valued predicates in Knowledge Bases (KBs), which involves structured information about entities and predicates. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for question answering and knowledge representation, databases (cs.DB) for data storage and retrieval, computational linguistics (cs.CL) for natural language processing, machine learning (cs.LG) for modeling and prediction, and information retrieval (cs.IR) for search and recommendation systems. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
